00:31:46,864 --> 00:31:48,324
Dennis?

477
00:31:49,325 --> 00:31:50,576
Where you goin' at so early?

478
00:31:51,160 --> 00:31:53,662
I'm gonna go run,
and then I got lawn work later.

479
00:31:54,288 --> 00:31:55,623
You comin' back, right?

480
00:31:56,832 --> 00:31:58,334
What you mean am I comin' back?

481
00:31:59,668 --> 00:32:01,253
It's gonna be like that, huh?

482
00:32:02,630 --> 00:32:04,465
What do you mean? Like what?

483
00:33:19,498 --> 00:33:22,626
- Where to?
- Highlandtown. Flush out yo' base, trooper.

484
00:33:35,014 --> 00:33:37,224
- What up, spider?
- Hey.

485
00:33:38,309 --> 00:33:40,311
Thank you, but I know how I'm voting.

486
00:33:40,769 --> 00:33:42,354
I'm gonna be late for work.

487
00:33:42,563 --> 00:33:45,232
Miss Anna, is it ok if I stand out here
while you go vote?

488
00:33:45,733 --> 00:33:47,610
- Don't you go nowhere, boy.
- Yes, ma'am.

489
00:33:48,444 --> 00:33:51,363
So, what up, man?
So, how much they payin' you for this?

490
00:33:51,447 --> 00:33:54,533
They say like 40, but I gotta work
the whole day though.

491
00:33:54,617 --> 00:33:55,618
Know what I mean?

492
00:33:55,701 --> 00:33:57,119
Yo, spider.

493
00:34:03,292 --> 00:34:04,501
That was spider, right?

494
00:34:04,585 --> 00:34:05,961
- Yeah.
- Where he go?

495
00:34:08,631 --> 00:34:10,883
No, thank you, man. I can't vote.

496
00:34:10,966 --> 00:34:13,552
Conviction? Felony?

497
00:34:13,636 --> 00:34:15,095
Move on, man.

498
00:34:15,262 --> 00:34:16,722
A'ight, man.

499
00:34:16,805 --> 00:34:20,100
You see spider again, you tell him
he need to come past my gym.

500
00:34:20,351 --> 00:34:22,478
He ain't been round in weeks,
and we need to talk.

501
00:34:22,561 --> 00:34:23,646
A'ight.

502
00:34:25,481 --> 00:34:27,983
- Where's the older kid?
- I don't know.

503
00:34:28,067 --> 00:34:29,151
Ok. You're hired.

504
00:34:29,485 --> 00:34:31,820
Shove one of those
into every hand you can.

505
00:34:37,326 --> 00:34:38,869
Thank you very much.

506
00:34:45,042 --> 00:34:48,170
- Why you ain't at school?
- Ain't no school today.

507
00:34:48,379 --> 00:34:50,923
- One them Jew holidays?
- Election.

508
00:34:51,215 --> 00:34:52,758
So what you gonna do?

509
00:34:53,467 --> 00:34:54,885
Dunno. Hang.

510
00:34:54,969 --> 00:34:56,345
What'd I say about steppin' up?

511
00:34:56,845 --> 00:35:00,349
Brianna turn off the faucet.
We gotta make some rain.

512
00:35:00,683 --> 00:35:03,185
I'm gonna get dressed.
We go see bodie.

513
00:35:11,819 --> 00:35:14,613
Kid, I got something else for you.

514
00:35:15,197 --> 00:35:17,866
Put one in every door
between the expressway and Winchester,

515
00:35:18,075 --> 00:35:19,576
and from freemont to fulton.

516
00:35:19,702 --> 00:35:24,123
You can do it by yourself or get some friends,
but I'm gonna come past, make sure it's done.

517
00:35:24,206 --> 00:35:25,791
Ok. One in each door. Cool.

518
00:35:26,333 --> 00:35:28,085
This is for the day's work.

519
00:35:28,460 --> 00:35:29,670
Wow!

520
00:35:29,753 --> 00:35:32,423
That's your walk-around.
But don't you fail me.

521
00:35:32,715 --> 00:35:35,467
Took forever.
What's all this, son?

522
00:35:35,551 --> 00:35:38,971
Man said if I put these fliers in doors,
I can get paid.

523
00:35:39,888 --> 00:35:41,140
I'll come right home after.

524
00:35:41,223 --> 00:35:42,308
You right you will.

525
00:35:42,725 --> 00:35:44,643
You ain't in these streets no more.

526
00:35:45,686 --> 00:35:47,229
No, ma'am.

527
00:35:48,272 --> 00:35:49,982
Sounds like she mean it.

528
00:35:52,151 --> 00:35:55,112
- 11:00 news, huh?
- Shut up.

529
00:35:56,238 --> 00:35:59,283
I'm on this shit detail
because you wanted to stir the pot.

530
00:36:00,409 --> 00:36:02,494
Tomorrow,
if we bust open the braddock case,

531
00:36:02,745 --> 00:36:04,204
nobody's gonna give a fuck.

532
00:36:04,538 --> 00:36:05,831
Life is timing.

533
00:36:06,457 --> 00:36:08,167
No shit, fucknuts.

534
00:36:12,379 --> 00:36:13,589
How you doing?

535
00:36:13,881 --> 00:36:15,799
- He's a cute one.
- Thanks.

536
00:36:16,050 --> 00:36:17,676
Hope you're voting today.

537
00:36:17,760 --> 00:36:20,637
- I am.
- Who's it gonna be? Give me a hint. Come on.

538
00:36:20,763 --> 00:36:23,307
- Don't keep me in suspense.
- You don't have to worry.

539
00:36:23,390 --> 00:36:24,683
Appreciate it.

540
00:36:30,606 --> 00:36:33,108
Tommy carcetti, running for mayor.
Nice to meet ya.

541
00:36:34,818 --> 00:36:37,946
- How much longer?
- Wrap this up. We got a lot more places.

542
00:36:38,781 --> 00:36:42,534
Tommy carcetti. I knew your dad.
First district Democratic club.

543
00:36:42,618 --> 00:36:45,162
- No kidding.
- Just wanted to say you got my vote.

544
00:36:45,245 --> 00:36:47,539
- Thank you.
- They had their chance.

545
00:36:47,998 --> 00:36:51,001
- Look what shape the city's in.
- I hope to turn things around.

546
00:36:51,085 --> 00:36:54,380
- Thanks for your support.
- You expect politicians to steal...

547
00:36:54,463 --> 00:36:57,341
- I don't, actually.
- It's part of the game. I understand.

548
00:36:57,841 --> 00:37:02,596
But we took one dollar outta every three,
not two outta three, like these moolies.

549
00:37:02,846 --> 00:37:05,808
I mean, leave something
for the city, for Christ sake.

550
00:37:06,475 --> 00:37:08,936
Am I right? Best of luck, councilman.

551
00:37:12,356 --> 00:37:14,274
- Moolies?
- Sorry.

552
00:37:17,319 --> 00:37:18,737
Election fliers?

553
00:37:18,821 --> 00:37:21,198
Yeah, just run up,
stick 'em in mailboxes,

554
00:37:21,281 --> 00:37:22,616
screen doors, whatever.

555
00:37:22,699 --> 00:37:24,993
- What about the vacants?
- We ain't got to do them.

556
00:37:25,619 --> 00:37:27,037
Some blocks ain't nothing but.

557
00:37:27,121 --> 00:37:28,997
That's what I'm saying.
This be easy money.

558
00:37:29,081 --> 00:37:30,082
Don't wanna do it?

559
00:37:30,165 --> 00:37:31,583
- I do it.
- Me too.

560
00:37:31,667 --> 00:37:33,419
This shit'd be easier if we had a car.

561
00:37:33,502 --> 00:37:36,171
Dang, donut. I'm in enough trouble
with miss Anna as is.

562
00:37:36,588 --> 00:37:38,006
So, what up, Mike? You in?

563
00:37:38,966 --> 00:37:40,846
All right, then. I'll
holler at you later, boy.

564
00:37:46,014 --> 00:37:48,934
Look, namond's been...
What's the word?

565
00:37:49,017 --> 00:37:52,271
Inconsistent. Sometimes he do good,
then other times, he just...

566
00:37:52,354 --> 00:37:54,773
We talked about that.
He gonna do better.

567
00:37:56,024 --> 00:37:57,359
Ain't you?

568
00:37:57,526 --> 00:37:59,486
Election day special, two for two!

569
00:37:59,695 --> 00:38:01,572
- I don't know.
- I do.

570
00:38:01,989 --> 00:38:05,451
You gonna give this boy his own package
or there gonna be some drama.

571
00:38:05,993 --> 00:38:08,704
You want me to talk to wee-bey?
Maybe you wanna talk to him.

572
00:38:08,787 --> 00:38:10,789
I give you his number. He got a cell phone.

573
00:38:10,873 --> 00:38:13,959
That's not necessary.
I got all the respect in the world for bey.

574
00:38:14,084 --> 00:38:15,794
Then show some for his family.

575
00:38:22,593 --> 00:38:25,429
Make me proud, hear?

576
00:38:36,523 --> 00:38:37,691
Damn, boy.

577
00:38:37,816 --> 00:38:40,027
Your mama's what
niggers call a dragon lady.

578
00:38:40,486 --> 00:38:41,987
She don't blink.

579
00:38:42,571 --> 00:38:44,198
Yeah, gimme some insight, though.

580
00:38:44,698 --> 00:38:45,824
To what?

581
00:38:46,241 --> 00:38:47,910
Why you is what you is.

582
00:39:11,850 --> 00:39:14,353
Yo. What up? Where y'all goin'?

583
00:39:14,770 --> 00:39:17,731
- Hungry, man. I need to eat.
- Come on. Let's finish this.

584
00:39:18,106 --> 00:39:20,484
- Nah, yo. This shit is boring.
- Fuck it.

585
00:39:20,567 --> 00:39:23,654
I ain't gonna pay y'all
if you don't finish the job, so...

586
00:39:23,862 --> 00:39:25,447
You already got the money?

587
00:39:25,781 --> 00:39:27,658
If the motherfucker paid you already,

588
00:39:27,950 --> 00:39:29,451
why the hell are we still here?

589
00:39:29,535 --> 00:39:30,702
Cos this is the job.

590
00:39:31,119 --> 00:39:33,539
Shit, the man ain't got
nobody to blame but hisself.

591
00:39:33,789 --> 00:39:35,457
It's his fault for payin' up front.

592
00:39:35,541 --> 00:39:39,503
Yo, you need to split that money up
or something cos time is a-wastin'.

593
00:39:44,508 --> 00:39:46,218
Can't even finish a day's work.

594
00:39:48,554 --> 00:39:50,180
Get me something at least.

595
00:39:50,264 --> 00:39:52,099
- Lake trout.
- Soda too?

596
00:39:52,182 --> 00:39:54,393
- Yeah. Strawberry.
- A'ight. I got ya.

597
00:40:18,542 --> 00:40:20,335
- One, two.
- Yes.

598
00:40:22,087 --> 00:40:23,130
One, two.

599
00:40:26,049 --> 00:40:28,427
Hey. Where the crew at?

600
00:40:28,510 --> 00:40:31,972
Randy got 'em all some job
handin' out election fliers or whatever.

601
00:40:32,055 --> 00:40:34,099
You ain't wanna do that?

602
00:40:34,433 --> 00:40:37,185
Hell, no. It's bullshit, man.

603
00:40:37,519 --> 00:40:39,605
- I got a job too.
- Word?

604
00:40:39,688 --> 00:40:41,815
With bodie. I'm movin' the package.

605
00:40:43,692 --> 00:40:44,892
You wanna go in on it with me?

606
00:40:46,528 --> 00:40:49,740
You sure? We could work together.

607
00:40:50,157 --> 00:40:51,366
Nah, man, that's your thing.

608
00:40:52,534 --> 00:40:56,455
- Go do what you do.
- Yeah, a'ight. I'm gonna holler at you.

609
00:41:08,550 --> 00:41:10,218
She a cute one, ain't she?

610
00:41:12,721 --> 00:41:15,349
Yeah, boy. You know I love the women.

611
00:41:21,563 --> 00:41:23,565
Hey, you seen spider around any?

612
00:41:25,275 --> 00:41:29,237
He ain't been round the gym in like a
month. I leave messages, he don't call.

613
00:41:30,614 --> 00:41:33,325
I don't understand.
He was one of my best welterweights.

614
00:41:33,408 --> 00:41:35,118
Why would he just quit like that?

615
00:41:36,078 --> 00:41:37,746
Why don't you ask his moms?

616
00:41:42,417 --> 00:41:45,796
Well, shit. I was locked
up a good while, right.

617
00:41:46,004 --> 00:41:47,422
I mean, I ain't no angel.

618
00:41:48,799 --> 00:41:50,592
No. You ain't that.

619
00:42:00,227 --> 00:42:01,520
Thanks a lot, folks.

620
00:42:01,603 --> 00:42:03,605
Good job. Keep it up.
We're almost home.

621
00:42:04,981 --> 00:42:06,942
You're the best. The best.

622
00:42:07,818 --> 00:42:09,277
Heavy turnout all around.

623
00:42:09,569 --> 00:42:12,155
Big lines on the West Side
might be bad for us. I dunno...

624
00:42:12,239 --> 00:42:16,618
We're out here in west Baltimore,
the heart of his political base.

625
00:42:16,868 --> 00:42:19,955
- This is today?
- This is live, right now in Lafayette square.

626
00:42:20,038 --> 00:42:23,598
Clay Davis just said his whole organization
was out going door-to-door for Royce's ticket.

627
00:42:23,750 --> 00:42:27,254
- So much for laying back on the mayor.
- We paid $20,000 for this shit?

628
00:42:27,337 --> 00:42:30,090
He probably went to Royce
and shook him down for another 30.

629
00:42:30,173 --> 00:42:33,301
Motherfucker. Clay Davis
must know something we don't.

630
00:42:33,885 --> 00:42:36,346
He knows just enough to get paid twice.

631
00:42:36,638 --> 00:42:38,807
Gotta blame ourselves
for payin' him up front.

632
00:42:39,141 --> 00:42:40,517
Hey, it was worth a shot.

633
00:42:40,600 --> 00:42:43,186
Aides to the mayor told me
they are concerned...

634
00:42:46,231 --> 00:42:47,566
Thanks, yo.

635
00:42:54,281 --> 00:42:56,074
I'm-a get me a cold one.

636
00:43:28,774 --> 00:43:30,484
Grab the wall.

637
00:43:37,199 --> 00:43:38,533
Officer Walker.

638
00:43:47,793 --> 00:43:50,128
I ain't gonna be out here strapped.

639
00:43:53,840 --> 00:43:55,550
You gonna take that on a humble?

640
00:43:58,512 --> 00:44:00,472
You don't know there's rules to this game.

641
00:44:00,555 --> 00:44:02,224
- Rules?
- Yeah.

642
00:44:13,610 --> 00:44:15,487
Where your shotgun at, Mr. Omar?

643
00:44:15,862 --> 00:44:17,989
Y'all ain't got no charges here.

644
00:44:18,073 --> 00:44:21,743
- Charge is murder, motherfucker.
- Murder? Who I kill?

645
00:44:22,911 --> 00:44:23,954
Hey, Omar.

646
00:44:24,162 --> 00:44:26,373
- Mcnulty. What the hell goin' on here?
- You tell me.

647
00:44:26,581 --> 00:44:29,084
We got a warrant for a robbery murder.
In a store.

648
00:44:32,712 --> 00:44:34,047
Wagon's here.

649
00:44:42,180 --> 00:44:45,392
- Hey, yo, mcnulty, I need a phone.
- Fuck your phone.

650
00:44:47,435 --> 00:44:49,771
If I'm going to booking,
I need to make a call tonight, yo.

651
00:44:54,276 --> 00:44:58,530
410-958-6612.

652
00:44:59,948 --> 00:45:01,283
And let it ring.

653
00:45:03,410 --> 00:45:04,536
Here.

654
00:45:05,954 --> 00:45:07,539
- Hey.
- Yo, butchie. I'm locked up, yo.

655
00:45:07,622 --> 00:45:10,876
- What you need?
- No bail. They sayin' it's murder.

656
00:45:11,251 --> 00:45:13,628
Murder? Well, don't worry. I got ya.

657
00:45:23,346 --> 00:45:24,806
You some kinda democrat?

658
00:45:28,393 --> 00:45:30,937
Voter turnout was
heavy across the city

659
00:45:31,021 --> 00:45:32,856
with some precincts reporting lines

660
00:45:32,939 --> 00:45:35,150
as soon as the polls opened
at 7:00 this morning.

661
00:45:35,609 --> 00:45:39,321
Election officials, however,
reported few problems throughout the day.

662
00:45:39,613 --> 00:45:43,074
Now the polls have closed, officials
at the board of elections downtown

663
00:45:43,158 --> 00:45:46,119
have begun the tedious process
of tallying the vote,

664
00:45:46,202 --> 00:45:48,788
prepared for what could be a long night.

665
00:45:49,205 --> 00:45:53,043
With just over half of the city's
316 precincts reporting,

666
00:45:53,168 --> 00:45:57,339
councilman Thomas j. Carcetti
has a narrow lead of 2%.

667
00:45:57,839 --> 00:46:00,926
Traditionally, those precincts
that report latest

668
00:46:01,051 --> 00:46:03,011
tend to be from west Baltimore,

669
00:46:03,303 --> 00:46:06,514
which is expected to favor
mayor Royce in the late going.

670
00:46:14,189 --> 00:46:17,400
- How it go?
- Good. Nothin' to it.

671
00:46:19,569 --> 00:46:21,029
I'm countin' on you, na'.

672
00:46:31,206 --> 00:46:34,125
Exit polls done earlier
in the day in key precincts

673
00:46:34,250 --> 00:46:36,336
show voters divided over the challenges

674
00:46:36,419 --> 00:46:39,547
facing this city,
such as crime and education.

675
00:46:41,383 --> 00:46:43,718
Blake leyh: Robots in the hood

676
00:46:51,977 --> 00:46:53,937
Be quite an election.

677
00:46:54,020 --> 00:46:55,915
Since this race tightened
in the last couple of weeks,

678
00:46:55,939 --> 00:46:58,149
I've been saying that this election

679
00:46:58,358 --> 00:47:00,026
would be won on the ground.

680
00:47:00,110 --> 00:47:02,821
Whoever has the best
field operations will take it.

681
00:47:02,904 --> 00:47:05,240
It's all about the turnout,
and this is something...

682
00:47:05,323 --> 00:47:06,908
What about bond?

683
00:47:07,909 --> 00:47:09,744
Uh-huh, uh-huh.

684
00:47:11,162 --> 00:47:12,580
Yeah.

685
00:47:14,165 --> 00:47:16,042
All right. Talk to you in a few.

686
00:47:17,502 --> 00:47:19,671
Bond's running really
strong against demper.

687
00:47:20,463 --> 00:47:22,343
Looks like we might have
a new state's attorney.

688
00:47:22,966 --> 00:47:25,844
- What does that mean for you?
- Demper's Royce's boy.

689
00:47:26,302 --> 00:47:28,304
Dare to get your hopes up, Tommy.

690
00:47:29,556 --> 00:47:33,727
You know what? Let's get
outta here for a while, take a walk.

691
00:48:00,295 --> 00:48:01,504
I'll get your ass.

692
00:48:22,567 --> 00:48:24,819
- Pretty.
- A little ripe.

693
00:48:25,528 --> 00:48:28,907
Well, can't do anything about
the way the harbor smells.

694
00:48:29,282 --> 00:48:32,285
- People are gonna expect you to.
- I guess.

695
00:48:33,369 --> 00:48:36,164
- You sound confident.
- I have a feeling.

696
00:48:44,172 --> 00:48:46,007
Could be a great city again.

697
00:48:48,384 --> 00:48:49,761
Pull some jobs in here.

698
00:48:50,178 --> 00:48:52,055
People move back, fix up the houses.

699
00:48:54,224 --> 00:48:55,683
It's ringing again.

700
00:48:59,187 --> 00:49:00,188
Terri.

701
00:49:00,271 --> 00:49:03,483
- You should answer it.
- I don't need an update every five minutes.

702
00:49:03,566 --> 00:49:05,568
- We should go anyway.
- Do we have to?

703
00:49:05,652 --> 00:49:08,530
I'm sure they're frantic.
They don't know where you are.

704
00:49:12,951 --> 00:49:14,202
Yeah?

705
00:49:15,537 --> 00:49:17,038
Taking a walk with my wife.

706
00:49:24,003 --> 00:49:25,338
On our way.

707
00:49:32,804 --> 00:49:34,180
Royce is conceding.

708
00:49:34,931 --> 00:49:36,391
The West Side precincts came in

709
00:49:36,474 --> 00:49:39,060
and we pulled two outta five votes
in some precincts.

710
00:49:40,103 --> 00:49:41,563
We stole his base.

711
00:49:43,231 --> 00:49:44,232
We won.

712
00:49:45,900 --> 00:49:47,527
Are we happy about that?

713
00:49:50,363 --> 00:49:51,573
I think so.

714
00:49:53,992 --> 00:49:55,368
I think we are.

715
00:49:57,537 --> 00:49:58,538
Yeah.

716
00:50:04,294 --> 00:50:05,545
You sure?

717
00:50:27,358 --> 00:50:29,152
Thank you. Thank you.

718
00:50:35,783 --> 00:50:37,952
Thank you. Thank you. Thank you. Please.

719
00:50:38,953 --> 00:50:41,873
I want to thank you all
for your hard work and dedication.

720
00:50:42,248 --> 00:50:44,375
Give yourselves a hand. Come on.

721
00:50:49,130 --> 00:50:52,091
I just got off the phone
with mayor Royce and councilman gray.

722
00:50:52,175 --> 00:50:54,093
They were gracious. I asked for their help.

723
00:50:54,177 --> 00:50:56,304
I mean, we still have a
general election to win.

724
00:51:00,225 --> 00:51:02,644
Is there a republican candidate
for mayor in Baltimore?

725
00:51:02,727 --> 00:51:03,978
I'm not sure.

726
00:51:05,480 --> 00:51:07,065
But assuming we win, we still have...

727
00:51:07,148 --> 00:51:09,525
A lot of work to do to
turn this city around,

728
00:51:09,609 --> 00:51:12,403
and we need everyone,
everyone who's willing to join us

729
00:51:12,487 --> 00:51:15,156
in making a better
Baltimore for our children.

730
00:51:20,328 --> 00:51:21,728
I don't want to make a long speech,

731
00:51:21,788 --> 00:51:23,957
believe me, you don't want to hear it,

732
00:51:24,874 --> 00:51:26,434
so I'll thank each of you individually.

733
00:51:26,459 --> 00:51:28,169
But for tonight, let's celebrate!

734
00:51:38,012 --> 00:51:40,014
Tommy! Tommy! Tommy!

735
00:51:44,519 --> 00:51:47,063
How you doin'? Thanks. Hey.

736
00:51:47,772 --> 00:51:49,357
Damond.

737
00:51:49,774 --> 00:51:52,944
- I look forward to working with you.
- Congratulations to you, too.

738
00:51:53,027 --> 00:51:54,362
Thank you.

739
00:51:55,697 --> 00:51:58,283
- I'm going home.
- No, stay. I won't be long.

740
00:51:58,366 --> 00:52:01,202
Yeah, you will. It's your night.

741
00:52:02,662 --> 00:52:03,997
You know what...

742
00:52:04,080 --> 00:52:05,665
Tommy. Tommy.

743
00:52:05,748 --> 00:52:08,793
- Look what washed up on the beach.
- Congratulations, Mr. Mayor.

744
00:52:09,544 --> 00:52:12,630
Just came by to wish you well.
Looking forward to working with you.

745
00:52:12,714 --> 00:52:16,759
- Shouldn't you be dead to me?
- I took it easy on you, son.

746
00:52:17,176 --> 00:52:18,803
I coulda had you for twice as much.

747
00:52:19,804 --> 00:52:21,306
You got off cheap.

748
00:52:23,349 --> 00:52:24,642
He's right.

749
00:52:54,464 --> 00:52:55,965
Butchie sent us.

750
00:53:06,976 --> 00:53:08,436
What you in for?

751
00:53:08,895 --> 00:53:10,646
I'm here on a 22-55.

752
00:53:13,232 --> 00:53:14,776
I talked back.

753
00:53:21,449 --> 00:53:23,659
- Moolie?
- Moolie.

754
00:53:23,743 --> 00:53:26,871
- He said that in front of you?
- He made a point of it, in fact.

755
00:53:27,121 --> 00:53:29,374
You said I oughta shore up my base.

756
00:53:29,457 --> 00:53:32,335
- You didn't call him on it?
- The ironies of democracy.

757
00:53:32,460 --> 00:53:34,796
A vote's a vote.
And I never throw one back.

758
00:53:35,254 --> 00:53:37,423
Speaking of ballots,
did you vote for me?

759
00:53:37,632 --> 00:53:42,428
The sanctity of the voting booth
is a cornerstone of American democracy.

760
00:53:45,431 --> 00:53:47,558
I gotta go. You need a ride?

761
00:53:47,642 --> 00:53:50,228
- Yeah.
- Come here. You're the best.

762
00:53:50,311 --> 00:53:51,646
Thanks, Norman.

763
00:53:53,231 --> 00:53:54,774
- Yeah, you take a break.
- You got it.

764
00:53:54,857 --> 00:53:56,734
- One day. Two days.
- Come here, you.

765
00:53:58,069 --> 00:53:59,862
- Be good.
- I'm gonna call you.

766
00:53:59,946 --> 00:54:01,489
I have a feeling you might.

767
00:54:01,572 --> 00:54:04,492
We are family

768
00:54:04,575 --> 00:54:07,120
I've got my carcetti and me

769
00:54:10,081 --> 00:54:11,749
Good night.

770
00:54:13,835 --> 00:54:14,919
Ooh.

771
00:54:15,962 --> 00:54:18,506
- I should go, too.
- One for the road?

772
00:54:19,298 --> 00:54:20,425
Sure.

773
00:54:21,968 --> 00:54:22,969
Scotch ok?

774
00:54:23,177 --> 00:54:24,262
Sure.

775
00:54:30,184 --> 00:54:32,311
You know, I gotta admit, it feels good.

776
00:54:33,980 --> 00:54:35,440
You deserve it.

777
00:54:36,441 --> 00:54:37,775
You worked hard.

778
00:54:38,317 --> 00:54:39,694
I did. I do.

779
00:54:41,988 --> 00:54:43,156
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

780
00:54:49,871 --> 00:54:53,499
You know, when I took this job,
you promised me a win bonus.

781
00:54:53,875 --> 00:54:55,418
Well, you earned it.

782
00:55:20,443 --> 00:55:22,403
I can't do this. Not now.

783
00:55:23,112 --> 00:55:25,448
Oh! Come on, Tommy.

784
00:55:26,449 --> 00:55:27,742
You haven't changed.

785
00:55:28,409 --> 00:55:29,827
Hell, from what Norman tells me,

786
00:55:29,911 --> 00:55:33,039
you nearly fell off
the campaign trail for a blonde

787
00:55:33,581 --> 00:55:35,583
at the stonewall dinner two months ago.

788
00:55:35,917 --> 00:55:38,252
He had to drag you out of the bar.

789
00:55:39,837 --> 00:55:41,672
It's not that I don't want to...

790
00:55:41,756 --> 00:55:45,426
Oh, you're feeling a bit mayoral. Right.

791
00:55:46,427 --> 00:55:47,970
You're on stage now.

792
00:55:48,971 --> 00:55:50,389
Well, Tommy...

793
00:55:50,806 --> 00:55:54,685
Four years is a long time
for a fellow like you.

794
00:55:56,145 --> 00:55:58,314
This could be your last chance for a while.

795
00:56:16,165 --> 00:56:17,291
You sure?

796
00:56:21,671 --> 00:56:23,965
Maybe you have learned something.

797
00:56:37,228 --> 00:56:38,604
Write me a check.

